# README Maintenance

## Style

- Title with emoji: `# VibeSliding ✨`
- Bold tagline + conversational hook
- Em-dash descriptions: `**Feature** — Explanation`
- Emoji bullets sparingly (🚀 🎨 ⚡)
- Friendly closing with emojis

## Structure

1. Title + tagline
2. Why VibeSliding? 🚀 (benefits)
3. Features (emoji bullets)
4. Quick Start (2-3 commands max)
5. Pipeline (numbered steps with bash block)
6. Usage Examples (progressive complexity)
7. CLI Reference (one table per module: `src.research.cli`, `src.outline.cli`, `src.render.style.cli`, `src.render.cli`, `src.present.cli`)
8. Input/Output (work directory tree, outline format, render output)
9. Configuration (`.env` section table + provider routing)
10. License + friendly sign-off

## Canonical Paths

Source of truth for file naming lives in `src/core/paths.py`. Always cross-check when documenting:

- Image output dir: `work/image_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS/` (prefix `IMAGE_DIR_PREFIX`)
- Slide PNGs: `slide_p##_v##.png`
- PDFs go to `--work` dir: `presentation_slides_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.pdf`, `presentation_speech_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.pdf`
- Default outline: `work/outline_16.md`
- Research state: `work/research_state.json`

## Update When

- CLI options change (check Click decorators in `src/*/cli.py`)
- Dependencies in `requirements.txt` change
- Config sections/keys in `.env.example` change
- Path constants in `src/core/paths.py` change
- New pipeline steps or providers added
- Input/output file naming conventions change

## Rules

- No new .md files — all docs in README.md
- Bullets over paragraphs
- Code blocks over descriptions
- CLI reference tables must match Click `@click.option` decorators exactly
- Usage examples must use real paths (e.g. `work/image_...` not `work/slides_...`)
- Work directory tree must include all generated artifacts with correct naming
